# BalanceBoard.Core

## Orchestration

`BalanceBoardSession` owns the 50 ms poll loop scheduled on `ConnectionWorker` (STA). All WiimoteLib / Bluetooth calls go through `_worker.Invoke*`. Do not add a second poll path.

## Data flow

`BalanceBoardConnection` → `BalanceProcessor` → `VJoyController` + `InputSimulator`

## Key services

| Service | Role |
|---------|------|
| `ConnectionWorker` | STA thread for WiimoteLib, BT pairing, poll timer |
| `BalanceProcessor` | Tare, center, triggers, axis mapping |
| `VJoyController` | Acquire/update/relinquish vJoy device; coalesced axis writes |
| `InputSimulator` | SendInput for 8 action slots (incl. X1/X2) |
| `FeederProcessCleanup` | Kill competing feeders, wait for vJoy free |
| `ActionPresets` | Mutate `AppSettings` for named profiles |
| `JumpPresets` | Easy/Normal/Hard jump thresholds |
| `DeviceIdRules` | HID path extraction; block persisting simulated IDs |

## Models

- `ProcessedBalance` — output of processor; consumed by vJoy and input
- `AppSettings.Actions` — keys: Left, Right, Forward, Backward, Modifier, Jump, DiagonalLeft, DiagonalRight
- `UiDetailLevel`, `JumpLevel` — UI/accessibility settings

## Constraints

- No WPF references in Core
- WiimoteLib exceptions: catch in connection layer; benign dispose races during `[DISCONNECT]`
- `WiimoteCollectionHelper.ReleaseAll` after HID probes
